ionoscloud:logging/pipeline:Pipeline.description:
## Import

In order to import a Logging pipeline, you can define an empty Logging pipeline resource in the plan:

hcl

resource "ionoscloud_logging_pipeline" "example" {

}

The resource can be imported using the `location` and `pipeline_id`, for example:

```sh
$ pulumi import ionoscloud:logging/pipeline:Pipeline example {location}:{pipeline_id}
```

ionoscloud:logging/getPipeline:getPipeli.description:
The **Logging pipeline** datasource can be used to search for and return an existing Logging pipeline.
If a single match is found, it will be returned. If your search results in multiple matches, an error will be returned.

>   Only tokens are accepted for authorization in the **logging_pipeline** data source. Please ensure you are using tokens as other methods will not be valid.

## Example Usage

